---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Music — Musical Terms That Score Big"
  description="Musical terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. QUAVER (18pts), FUGUE (9pts), PIZZICATO (31pts), CHORD (11pts), TEMPO (9pts). Expand your rack with music vocabulary."
  keywords="scrabble music words, quaver scrabble points, fugue scrabble, pizzicato scrabble, chord scrabble word, tempo scrabble, musical terms scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Music — Musical Terms That Score Big","description":"Musical terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. QUAVER (18pts), FUGUE (9pts), PIZZICATO (31pts), CHORD (11pts), TEMPO (9pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-music"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is QUAVER a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. QUAVER scores 18 points (Q=10, U=1, A=1, V=4, E=1, R=1). It means a musical note equal to an eighth note and is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play PIZZICATO in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! PIZZICATO scores 31 points (P=3, I=1, Z=10, Z=10, I=1, C=3, A=1, T=1, O=1) and uses both Z tiles. It's a 9-letter word requiring a bingo or existing letters on the board."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best short music words for Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"CHORD (11pts), TEMPO (9pts), FUGUE (9pts), FORTE (8pts), and CLEF (9pts) are all strong 4-5 letter plays using common tiles with good scoring."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Music — Musical Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Music vocabulary offers Scrabble players a rich vein of unusual but perfectly valid words. From the Q-heavy QUAVER to the double-Z monster PIZZICATO, these terms combine familiar concepts with strong letter values. Learning music words gives you options for premium tiles that other players miss entirely.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">31 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PIZZICATO (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUAVER</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CHORD</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TEMPO</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Scoring Music Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">PIZZICATO — 31 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">P=3, I=1, Z=10, Z=10, I=1, C=3, A=1, T=1, O=1 · 9 letters · Uses both Z tiles</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A technique of plucking strings instead of bowing. At 31 base points using both Z tiles, PIZZICATO is a devastating play. You'll need a bingo or existing letters on the board to play all 9 tiles — but with a blank for one Z, it becomes more achievable.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎵 QUAVER</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">18 pts · Q=10, U=1, A=1, V=4, E=1, R=1 · Eighth note</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎶 CHORD</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · C=3, H=4, O=1, R=1, D=2 · Three+ notes together</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎹 FUGUE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · F=4, U=1, G=2, U=1, E=1 · Contrapuntal composition</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎼 TEMPO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · T=1, E=1, M=3, P=3, O=1 · Speed of music</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Medium-Scoring Music Vocabulary</h2>
      <p>These 6-10 point words use common tiles and fit easily on most boards:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CLEF</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FORTE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">STAVE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LYRIC</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CELLO</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OBOE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategic Tips for Music Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUAVER burns Q safely:</span> Unlike QI or QOPH, QUAVER uses common letters alongside Q+U. When you draw Q, QUAVER is one of the most natural plays at 18 points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CHORD uses the H powerfully:</span> At 11 points from 5 tiles, CHORD leverages C=3, H=4, and D=2. The H often sits unused — pair it with CH for familiar music terms.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">FUGUE for vowel-heavy racks:</span> With three vowels (U, U, E), FUGUE is ideal when your rack has too many vowels. The F=4 and G=2 add scoring punch.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Music words excel at burning <span class="text-white font-medium">problem tiles</span> — Q (QUAVER), double-Z (PIZZICATO), excess vowels (FUGUE, OBOE), and H (CHORD). Keep a mental list of 5 music words and you'll always have an exit strategy for tough racks.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-music-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Music Words — Highest Scoring Musical Vocabulary</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-q-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Q Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-science/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Science</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid music word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
